  "question_text": "<h3>Word Search II</h3><p>Find all words from an array of strings in a 2D board.</p>",
  "difficulty": "HARD",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "2D grid, array of strings.",
  "output_format": "Array of strings.",
  "constraints": [
    "m, n <= 12",
    "words <= 1000"
  ],
  "explanation": "Store words in a Trie for efficient prefix checking. Perform DFS on every board cell to find paths matching Trie words.",
  "answer": "def findWords(board, words):\n    trie = {};\n    for w in words:\n        node = trie\n        for c in w: node = node.setdefault(c, {})\n        node[\"#\"] = w\n    res = set(); r, c = len(board), len(board[0])\n    def dfs(i, j, node, vis):\n        if \"#\" in node: res.add(node[\"#\"])\n        for ni, nj in [(i+1,j),(i-1,j),(i,j+1),(i,j-1)]:\n            if 0<=ni<r and 0<=nj<c and board[ni][nj] in node and (ni,nj) not in vis:\n                dfs(ni, nj, node[board[ni][nj]], vis | {(ni,nj)})\n    for i in range(r):\n        for j in range(c):\n            if board[i][j] in trie:\n                dfs(i, j, trie[board[i][j]], {(i,j)})\n    return list(res)",
  "boilerplate": {
